    "original_title": "Brooklyn: Hamilton Avenue - Columbia Street",
    "text": "Hamilton Avenue, east side, frori Columbia Street (right) to Woodhull Street, showing two brick buildings that were later demolished. Cn its site was erected a Socony gasoline station. The two houses form a triangle made up of the three above-mentioned thoroughfares. Columbia Street can be seen running in a northeasterly direction on the right; o the extreme left is a house on\nWoodhull Street.\nMarch 27, 1931\nP. L. Sperr\n(2)\nThe same site, showing the Socony gas station which replaced the old buildings. On the right are houses on Columbia Street; across the left corner of the gas station are those on\nWoodhull Street.\n",
